HOUSE BILL 238
I1, P1 6lr0062
(PRE–FILED) CF SB 226
By: Chair, Economic Matters Committee (By Request – Departmental – Planning)
Requested: September 16, 2025
Introduced and read first time: January 14, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters and Government, Labor, and Elections
Committee Report: Favorable
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 3, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Heritage Area Authority and Heritage Areas – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of altering the voting membership of the Maryland Heritage Area
4 Authority; increasing the number of voting members of the Authority that
5 constitutes a quorum; repealing the requirement that the Authority send copies of
6 boundary maps to certain county clerks; repealing the requirement that certain
7 State officials develop certain program statements and instead requiring certain
8 State officials and certain units of State government to support and assist certain
9 activities in certified heritage areas in certain ways; authorizing the Authority to
10 award certain grants and loans for certain purposes in a certain manner; repealing
11 certain requirements for certain grants and loans; and generally relating to the
12 Maryland Heritage Area Authority and heritage areas.
13 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
14 Article – Financial Institutions
15 Section 13–1104(a), 13–1105, 13–1110(d) and (e), 13–1112, and 13–1113
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Financial Institutions
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0238*

2 HOUSE BILL 238
1 13–1104.
2 (a) The Authority consists of:
3 (1) The Secretary of Housing and Community Development;
4 (2) The Secretary of Commerce;
5 (3) The Secretary of Higher Education;
6 (4) The Secretary of Transportation;
7 (5) The Secretary of Natural Resources;
8 (6) The Secretary of [the Department of] Planning;
9 (7) THE SECRETARY OF AGRICULTURE;
10 (8) THE STATE SUPERINTENDENT OF SCHOOLS;
11 [(7)] (9) The State Historic Preservation Officer; and
12 [(8)] (10) Ten members appointed by the Governor with the advice and
13 consent of the Senate:
14 (i) Two of whom shall be elected officials or representatives of local
15 jurisdictions;
16 (ii) Two of whom shall be appointed from names recommended by
17 the President of the Maryland Senate;
18 (iii) Two of whom shall be appointed from names recommended by
19 the Speaker of the House of Delegates;
20 (iv) [One of whom is a public member of the Maryland Greenways
21 Commission;
22 (v)] One of whom is a public member of the Maryland Tourism
23 Development Board;
24 (V) ONE OF WHOM IS A MEMBER OF THE PUBLIC WHO HAS
25 SIGNIFICANT EDUCATION OR EXPERIENCE IN NATURAL RESOURCE STEWARDSHIP
26 OR CLIMATE RESILIENCY;
27 (vi) One of whom is a member of the public who has significant
28 education or experience in historic preservation; and

HOUSE BILL 238 3
1 (vii) One of whom is a member of the public who has significant
2 education or experience in heritage tourism.
3 13–1105.
4 (a) [Nine] TEN voting members of the Authority are a quorum.
5 (b) An action of the Authority must receive the affirmative vote of at least a
6 majority of the voting members of the Authority.
7 (c) The Authority shall determine the times and places of its meetings.
8 (d) A member of the Authority:
9 (1) May not receive compensation; but
10 (2) Is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
11 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
12 13–1110.
13 (d) (1) The boundaries for each recognized heritage area are the boundaries
14 depicted on the map accompanying each proposal as approved by the Authority.
15 (2) After initial approval by the Authority of the boundaries of a recognized
16 heritage area, the Authority may amend or revise the boundaries:
17 (i) With the approval of all of the local jurisdictions where the
18 property to be added or removed is located; and
19 (ii) On publication in the Maryland Register of a revised drawing,
20 boundary description, or Uniform Resource Locator (URL) to a geographical information
21 system file.
22 (3) Boundary maps for each recognized heritage area shall be kept on file
23 at the Authority.
24 [(4) The Authority shall send a copy of each boundary map to the office of
25 the county clerk where the recognized heritage area is located.]
26 (e) Designation of a heritage area by the Authority as a recognized heritage area
27 establishes eligibility for [matching] grant assistance for the development of management
28 plans.
29 13–1112.

4 HOUSE BILL 238
1 (a) [(1)] The State officials under items [(i)] (1) through [(vii)] (9) of this
2 subsection who have program responsibilities that affect aspects of the interpretation,
3 preservation, development, and use of heritage area resources shall [prepare a program
4 statement detailing actions] SUPPORT AND ASSIST ACTIVITIES IN CERTIFIED
5 HERITAGE AREAS in the areas of planning, development, use, IMPLEMENTATION,
6 assistance, and regulation [that support and assist the establishment and management of
7 certified heritage areas], as follows:
8 [(i)] (1) Secretary of Planning regarding local government
9 adoption of heritage area management plans and regarding historic preservation and
10 museum programs;
11 [(ii)] (2) Secretary of Housing and Community Development
12 regarding housing and neighborhood revitalization;
13 [(iii)] (3) Secretary of Commerce regarding the State tourism
14 program and economic development and job creation activities;
15 [(iv)] (4) Secretary of Natural Resources regarding outdoor
16 recreation and the management of natural resources, including State greenways;
17 [(v)] (5) Secretary of Higher Education regarding educational
18 resources and their interpretation;
19 [(vi)] (6) Secretary of Transportation regarding access to and
20 transportation within certified heritage areas, including the scenic byways program and
21 programs for special signage; [and]
22 [(vii)] (7) Secretary of General Services regarding the management
23 and disposition of State property;
24 (8) SECRETARY OF AGRICULTURE REGARDING AGRICULTURAL
25 RESOURCES WITHIN CERTIFIED HERITAGE AREAS; AND
26 (9) STATE SUPERINTENDENT OF SCHOOLS REGARDING
27 EDUCATIONAL RESOURCES AND THEIR INTERPRETATION WITHIN CERTIFIED
28 HERITAGE AREAS.
29 [(2) The State officials shall submit the program statements required under
30 paragraph (1) of this subsection, and any revisions of the statements, to the Authority.]
31 (b) Units of State government that conduct or support AND ASSIST activities
32 affecting a certified heritage area shall:

HOUSE BILL 238 5
1 (1) Consult, cooperate, and to the maximum extent feasible, coordinate
2 their activities with the unit or entity responsible for the management of each certified
3 heritage area;
4 (2) To the maximum extent practicable, carry out the activities of the unit
5 in a manner that is consistent with the approved management plan for the certified
6 heritage area; and
7 (3) When conducting a review of activities under §§ 5A–325 and
8 5A–326 of the State Finance and Procurement Article, assure that the activities will not
9 have an adverse effect on the historic and cultural resources of the certified heritage area,
10 unless there is no prudent and feasible alternative.
11 13–1113.
12 (a) As provided in the State budget, AND ON TERMS AND CONDITIONS THE
13 AUTHORITY ESTABLISHES, the Authority may award:
14 (1) Grants and loans to local jurisdictions or other appropriate entities for
15 planning, design, acquisition, development, preservation, restoration, interpretation,
16 marketing, and programming of certified heritage areas; and
17 (2) Grants to local jurisdictions or other appropriate entities to [develop]:
18 (I) DEVELOP management plans in recognized heritage areas; AND
19 (II) ENCOURAGE REVITALIZATION OF AND REINVESTMENT IN
20 CERTIFIED HERITAGE AREA RESOURCES.
21 (B) IN AWARDING A GRANT OR LOAN UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
22 SECTION, THE AUTHORITY MAY REQUIRE MATCHING FUNDS IN WHATEVER
23 PROPORTION THE AUTHORITY CONSIDERS APPROPRIATE.
24 [(b) A grant to develop a management plan may not exceed 50% of the cost of the
25 management plan.
26 (c) An acquisition or development grant:
27 (1) May not be used for any purpose other than implementation of the
28 certified heritage area in conformity with the approved management plan; and
29 (2) May not exceed 50% of the total project cost for which the grant is
30 awarded.
31 (d) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Authority may make
32 program grants to local jurisdictions and other appropriate entities:

6 HOUSE BILL 238
1 (i) To develop and present interpretive exhibits, materials or other
2 appropriate products to further the educational and recreational objectives of the certified
3 heritage areas program; and
4 (ii) To encourage revitalization of, and reinvestment in, certified
5 heritage area resources.
6 (2) A program grant made by the Authority under paragraph (1) of this
7 subsection may not exceed 50% of the estimated project cost.]
8 [(e)] (C) Through the resources of the members of the Authority and in
9 cooperation with other State agencies, the Authority shall provide technical assistance to
10 management entities implementing a management plan.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the term of the initial member
12 of the Maryland Heritage Area Authority who is a member of the public with significant
13 education or experience in natural resource stewardship or climate resiliency under §
14 13–1104 of the Financial Institutions Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, shall serve
15 the remainder of the term of the public member of the Maryland Greenways Commission
16 until a successor is appointed and qualifies.
17 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
